Now I can see the key issue. Let me look at `add_header` and `add_leading_header` more carefully:

```javascript
add_header(key, value) {
    this.header.add_end(key, value)
    if (this.header_pos > 0) this.reset_headers()
}

add_leading_header(key, value) {
    this.header.add(key, value)
    if (this.header_pos > 0) this.reset_headers()
}

reset_headers() {
    const header_lines = this.header.lines()
    this.header_pos = header_lines.length
}
```

The problem is that `add_header` and `add_leading_header` add headers to `this.header` but then `reset_headers` only updates `this.header_pos`. It does NOT actually reset the `message_stream`'s header lines. When `add_data` was called, `header_lines` were pushed to `this.header_lines[]`, and the `message_stream` was built with `this.header.header_list`. But `reset_headers` doesn't update the `message_stream` with the new header lines.

